(284, 'Triangle Fraternity Educational Outreach Scholarship', '', 'Scholarships will be awarded based on character and merit for <strong>first-year male STEM majors</strong>. Judgment will be based off of the individual’s application, first college semester GPA, and personal interviews. Award amounts will be between 200 and 1,000 dollars and will be awarded to the top outstanding gentlemen, up to 10 may be chosen. An applicant must be in his first year at Ohio State and majoring in an engineering, science, math, or architecture field. If an interested applicant’s major is engineering undecided, or they are changing into an eligible major, they are eligible and encouraged to apply. Undecided or exploration majors are judged eligible on an individual basis. Fraternal involvement with Triangle fraternity will not be a factor in judgments.<br><strong>Preliminary application must be submitted by December 1st for full consideration.</strong> Send physical applications to 45 E Lane Columbus, OH or email to <a href="mailto:Jacobs.272@osu.edu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Jacobs.272@osu.edu</a> . Scholarship interviews will be scheduled after the initial application is received. GPA from applicants first semester at OSU will be used as a factor in award judgment. Scholarships will be awarded in January. <strong><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdlm_ccTxWGOi4om6mBXP6xm406XOPxNX_aEwyoNy8MCku2_w/formResponse" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Fill out the online form here to apply.</a></strong>', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-11-21T00:00:00', '2016-11-21T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(282, 'Football @ Michigan State', '', 'null', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-19T12:00:00', '2016-11-19T15:00:00', 2, 0),
(283, 'Summer Program in Biostatistics & Computational Biology at the Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health', 'Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health', 'The Summer Program is an intensive 6-week program, during which qualified participants (from underrepresented groups in graduate education) receive a whirlwind introduction to biostatistics, epidemiology, and public health research. This program is designed to expose undergraduates to the use of quantitative methods for biological, environmental, and medical research.<br><a href="https://www.hsph.harvard.edu/biostatistics/diversity/summer-program/eligibility-application/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Consider applying and note the requirements here!</a>', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-11-21T00:00:00', '2016-11-21T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(280, 'Columbus Zoo Wildlights', '', 'Come see the Columbus Zoo Wildlights with other Arts and Sciences Scholars Programs. Admission to the zoo is free, <em>if you bring along 5 canned food items</em> to donate to the Mid-Ohio Foodbank. <strong>Meet at 4:00pm in front of Baker East</strong> to ride a CABS bus. We are limited to 30 STEM EE Scholars, please <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeA__MCmJsYM88G9cv75Synf9hmkRzy_4WYq9XrfgWRdE6Hhw/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">RSVP</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-18T16:00:00', '2016-11-18T20:30:00', 2, 0),
(279, 'Modeling and State Implementation of Regulatory Measures for Ohio''s Air Quality', 'Smith Lab, 3150', '<em>For student interested in the environmental regulation, public health and statistical models</em><br>The Ohio Environmental Protection Agency is a<strong> State Agency dedicated to protecting the environment and public health</strong> by ensuring compliance with environmental laws and demonstrating leadership in environmental stewarship.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-18T15:00:00', '2016-11-18T16:00:00', 2, 0),
(278, 'Healthy Places: Designing Cities for Walking and Biking', 'Thompson Library, 165 ', '<em>Students interested in Technology, Engineering and Mathematics </em><br>The Columbus Collaboratory will share some of the <strong>cutting edge technologies in development for their member companies,</strong> including a demo of CognizeR, the package developed for integrating IBM’s Watson into R.A panel on how Columbus and other cities are working to improve livability and encourage active transportation will feature speakers from the College of Engineering, Mid-Ohio Regional Planning Commission, Columbus Public Health, and YayBikes! Topics to include the use of mobility data and research to inform public policy decisions. A light meal will be served.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-18T11:45:00', '2016-11-18T13:00:00', 2, 0),
(277, 'H&S Fall Fest', 'Honors & Scholars Kuhn House', 'This year''s HSPB Fall Fest, at the Honors &amp; Scholars Kuhn House, will be held from 7:00 to 9:00 p.m. on November 17! Come to Fall Fest to learn about fall traditions around the world, enjoy free food, make thanksgiving door-decorations for Nationwide Children''s Hospital, and more! Bring your friends, and we''ll see you there!', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-11-17T19:00:00', '2016-11-17T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(275, 'ACMW: CS Technical Interview Workshop', 'Dreese 264', '<em>This event is recommended for computer science majors</em><br>Attend this ACMW (Association of Machinery-Women''s Chapter) workshop to sharpen your interview skills and gain valuable insight about the internship application process. Hear from past interns at Google, Microsoft, and local Columbus tech companies!', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-16T19:00:00', '2016-11-16T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(276, 'A Career in National Labs', 'Physics Research Building', 'Learn more about diverse career paths in the STEM disciplines from Ohio State alumni working in industry. <a href="http://cem.osu.edu/files/2016/08/CEM-Alumni-Career-Series-Sergei-Manuilov-3M.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Click here for more info.</a>', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-17T11:30:00', '2016-11-17T12:30:00', 2, 0),
(274, 'OUAB Flicks for Free, ft. Snowden', 'Ohio Union, U.S. Bank Conference Theater', 'First show: 6 PM<br>Second show: 8:30 PM<br>Free popcorn and beverages will be provided!<br><em>Disillusioned with the intelligence community, top contractor Edward Snowden (Joseph Gordon-Levitt) leaves his job at the National Security Agency. He now knows that a virtual mountain of data is being assembled to track all forms of digital communication -- not just from foreign governments and terrorist groups, but from ordinary Americans. When Snowden decides to leak this classified information, he becomes a traitor to some, a hero to others and a fugitive from the law.</em>', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-16T18:00:00', '2016-11-16T22:00:00', 2, 0),
(272, 'Preparing Papers', 'Dennis Learning Center', 'For this workshop, you will learn how to <strong>create strong thesis statements, introductions, body paragraphs and conclusions</strong> for any paper you have to write. You will learn how to combat writer’s block. We also will train you how to appropriately document supporting materials and avoid plagiarism at all costs.<br>To register for this event, click <a href="http://fye.osu.edu/successseries.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-16T10:30:00', '2016-11-16T11:15:00', 2, 0),
(273, '2nd Year Scholars Monthly Meeting (Make-Up Meeting)', 'Mendenhall Lab 115', 'Capstone Project Hours Log<br><a href="https://osu.az1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_882L66zhKtdQACx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://osu.az1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_882L66zhKtdQACx</a>', 'teamup', '2155500', '2016-11-16T16:00:00', '2016-11-16T17:30:00', 2, 0),
(271, 'Workshop: Social Media Mining', 'Hitchcock 031', '<em>This event will be useful for students in math and engineering, particularly CSE/CIS and Data Analytics.</em><br>A workshop demonstrating the use of<strong> Python to scrape data from Twitter and Facebook</strong> and as a general web scraping tool. Attendees can watch or follow along through the process. All scripts and instructions will be shared beforehand.<br> ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-15T19:30:00', '2016-11-15T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(270, 'Navigating the Internship Application Process', 'Macquigg Laboratory 264', '<em>This event is recommended for students interested in summer internships, with a particular focus on engineering and arts &amp; sciences.</em><br>Second years Alice Li and Stephen Wu will be talking about the <strong>internship application process</strong>. Learn how to set yourself apart from other applicants, get ahead in the job search, and get tips about the process. Topics include: side projects, resumes, career fairs, interviews, technical and behavorial questions, and healthy expectations. <br>Alice is a second year Actuarial Science and Computer Information Science major; Stephen is a Computer Science Engineering major. Learn about some of their experiences in applying to over 70 places, attending 5 career fairs, and interviewing and interacting with various employers. ', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-11-15T16:10:00', '2016-11-15T17:15:00', 2, 0),
(269, 'Udall Scholarship Informational Session', 'Kuhn Honors & Scholars House', 'The Udall Scholarship awards $7,000 to recognize outstanding<strong> sophomores and juniors committed to careers related to the environment, or to Native American students pursuing careers related to tribal policy/tribal health care</strong>. Forty scholarships will be awarded in the environmental category; twenty scholars will be selected for students passionate about Indian country. Successful applicants will not only have plans to become environmental or tribal leaders, but will have already begun demonstrating this commitment through related activities, research, academics, and job/internship experience. At this info session, we will discuss the Udall program, scholarship application, and selection process and criteria. Students interested in Ohio State''s nomination for the Udall must submit a campus application by February 13, 2017. More information can be found on the Udall''s website, http://<a href="http://www.udall.gov/OurPrograms/Scholarship/Scholarship.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">www.udall.gov/OurPrograms/Scholarship/Scholarship.aspx</a>.<br>Two sessions will be held this week: 11/15 4-4:30PM and 11/18 2-2:30PM ', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-11-15T14:00:00', '2016-11-15T14:30:00', 2, 0),
(268, 'Translational Data Analytics Forum Poster Session', 'Blackwell Inn and Conference Center ', '<em>This event is recommended for data analytics and actuarial science majors. </em><br>Ohio State postdoctoral researchers, graduate and undergraduate students, faculty, and staff present on their data analytics and decision science research. This is a unique opportunity to talk about research, meet others working the area of analytics and data science, and connect with potential collaborators across campus.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-14T13:00:00', '2016-11-14T15:00:00', 2, 0),
(267, 'Honda Guest Lecture: Vehicle Development Process, Geometric & Structural Digital Design', 'E100 Scott Lab', 'This discussion will briefly cover Honda’s overall development flow and the digital tools used to design a vehicle. The complexity of such systems requires multiple design iterations first between Styling and Body Design groups and then between Body Design and Manufacturing Groups. Full digital representations of vehicles enables critical and rapid communications within Honda between Styling, Design and Manufacturing.  The lecture will discuss project data management, good digital modeling and best practices for geometric modeling of vehicle body structures and flexible parametrics in the design process.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-14T12:40:00', '2016-11-14T13:40:00', 2, 0),
(266, 'Military Mental Health Symposium ', 'Ohio Union’s U.S. Bank Conference Theater', '<em>For students interested in health sciences and psychology</em><br>General Mark Graham (Ret.) and Carol Graham will share their story, which is featured in the book The Invisible Front: Love and Loss in an Era of Endless War. This military family is dedicated to addressing the <strong>military’s mental health crisis</strong> after losing both their sons in military service — one in combat and one to suicide. The event also includes a book signing and panel discussion. ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-14T09:00:00', '2016-11-14T12:00:00', 2, 0),
(265, 'Honors & Scholars Autumn Enrichment Grant', '', 'Working toward the Honors &amp; Scholars mission of providing students the ability to participate in opportunities that help create a holistic learning experience, the Honors &amp; Scholars Center will award $100,000 annually in student enrichment grants thanks solely to donor contributions. The scholarship amount will range based on the student''s proposals, with a maximum award of $3,000, and will be awarded through a competitive application process. <br>Funds are available to undergraduate Honors and Scholars students of all majors and can be utilized for a variety of purposes, including, but not limited to research, creative work and study abroad. Applicants must be current, full-time undergraduate students at the Columbus campus, and be in good standing in the University Honors Program or an Ohio State Scholars Program. The project or experience must enhance a student''s academic experience and learning, and take place before they graduate. The experiences will need to highlight and include the Honors &amp; Scholars <a href="http://honors-scholars.osu.edu/documents/goals.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">G.O.A.L.S</a>,: Global awareness, Original inquiry, Academic enrichment, Leadership development and Service engagement.<br><strong><a href="https://hsapp.osu.edu/student_enrichment_grants/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Click here to apply for the Autumn Enrichment Grant Competition</a> before November 25th!</strong>', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-11-14T00:00:00', '2016-11-14T23:59:00', 2, 0),
