(264, 'Science Sundays: Sian Block on "How to perform your best under stress"', 'Ohio Union, U.S. Bank Conference Theatre', 'In an energetic tour of the latest brain science, Sian Beilock explains why we all too often blunder when the stakes are high. She reveals what happens in our brain and body when we experience performance anxiety and shows us how to succeed brilliantly when it matters most. Sian Beilock, psychology professor and director, Human performance Lab, University of Chicago, is author of the bestseller, Choke.<br><a href="https://stemoutreach.osu.edu/events/science-sundays-sian-block-how-perform-your-best-under-stress" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">The lecture will be from 3 to 4 pm, in the Ohio Union U.S. Bank Conference Theatre. A reception will follow from 4 to 5 pm, in the Ohio Union Ohio Staters Traditions Room.</a>', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-13T15:00:00', '2016-11-13T16:00:00', 2, 0),
(260, 'Women''s Volleyball', 'St. John Arena', 'null', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-11T19:00:00', '2016-11-11T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(261, 'Maryland Football Watch / Tailgate Party', 'Houston House, TBD', 'Come out and enjoy an afternoon watching the Buckeyes crush Maryland on November 12th from 3:00pm-7:30pm! We will also have crafts, face painting, and board games! Pizza and refreshments will be provided.<br>Please <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/3MS9RWT" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">RSVP and let us know what pizza, drinks, or games you would like</a>! Feel free to bring stuff to do as well. ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-12T15:00:00', '2016-11-12T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(258, 'Veteran''s Day - No Classes', '', 'No classes, offices closed.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-11T00:00:00', '2016-11-11T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(259, 'Data Science Workshop', '', '<em>This two-day seminar is for students interested in data analytics and will provide the essentials of data science in the finance industry and python programming. This event is recommended for CSE/CIS, Data Analytics, and Actuarial Science majors. </em><br>DATES: 12 – 13 November 2016 <br>COURSE LENGTH: 2 days <br>TIME: 09:30am – 5:00pm each day<br>$149 per ticket, using discount code: BuckeyesIDS2016. <br>The Big Data &amp; Analytics Association will soon be hosting Cognitir, a world-renown company originally founded in Europe. They will hold a workshop on the analytics and <strong>data science in Finance</strong>. This is a 2-day weekend event (<strong>Nov 12 &amp; 13) </strong>which will result in a <strong>Python certification</strong>. <br>To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.cognitir.com/osu/ids-finance" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">http://www.cognitir.com/osu/ids-finance</a>  or click <a href="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/0724670675ea259cb94841576/files/Finance_Analytics_Workshop_BDAA_Cognitir.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a> for the syllabus.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-12T00:00:00', '2016-11-13T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(257, 'Gearing Up for Higher Ed', 'Dennis Learning Center', 'The gearing up for higher education workshop was developed to help you know what it really takes to succeed in college. It will help you apply <strong>strategies for managing time, learning from texts and lectures and preparing for exams</strong> that will help you thrive in the context of a university.<br>To register for this event, click <a href="http://fye.osu.edu/successseries.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-10T15:00:00', '2016-11-10T15:45:00', 2, 0),
(256, 'OUAB Flicks for Free: ft. War Dogs', 'Ohio Union, U.S. Bank Conference Theater', 'First show: 6 PM<br>Second show: 8:30 PM<br>Location: U.S. Bank Conference Theater (Ohio Union)<br>Free popcorn and beverages will be provided!<br><em>Two friends in their early 20s (Hill and Teller) living in Miami Beach during the Iraq War exploit a little-known government initiative that allows small businesses to bid on U.S. Military contracts. Starting small, they begin raking in big money and are living the high life. But the pair gets in over their heads when they land a 300 million dollar deal to arm the Afghan Military - a deal that puts them in business with some very shady people, not the least of which turns out to be the U.S. Government. Based on true events.<em></em></em>', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-09T20:30:00', '2016-11-09T22:00:00', 2, 0),
(255, 'OSU Graduate and Professional School Fair', 'Ohio Union Great Hall Meeting Rooms 1, 2 and 3', 'The seventh annual OSU Graduate and Professional School Fair will be held on Wednesday, November 9 in the Ohio Union Great Hall Meeting Rooms 1, 2 and 3. Admission representatives from more than twenty OSU programs, pre-law and pre-health advisors, and arts and sciences career counselors will be available to answer questions. This is a good opportunity for students who are approaching graduation to learn what they need to do in order to apply to an OSU program. It is also a great opportunity for students who are new to OSU to begin to think about coursework, extracurricular activities, and co-curricular opportunities that will help them to prepare for graduate or professional school admission. This Fair is an option for Student Success Series credit. Admission is free and refreshments will be provided. This program is presented by the College of Arts and Sciences Student Council.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-09T16:30:00', '2016-11-09T18:30:00', 2, 0),
(254, '2nd Year Scholars Monthly Meeting', 'Mendenhall Lab 115', 'Please come with an<strong> updated version of your resume and/or CV</strong> and a<strong> draft introductory paragraph</strong> for your 2nd year project. See the previous email for more details. <br>Capstone Project Hours Log: <a href="https://osu.az1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_882L66zhKtdQACx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://osu.az1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_882L66zhKtdQACx</a>', 'teamup', '2155500', '2016-11-09T16:00:00', '2016-11-09T17:30:00', 2, 0),
(253, 'Byrd Polar Lecture: Global Climate Change', 'Macquigg Laboratory 264', 'The Byrd Polar and Climate Research Center (BPCRC) at <a href="http://www.osu.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">The Ohio State University</a> is recognized internationally as a leader in polar, alpine, and climate research. Our research programs are conducted throughout the world. The Center is named in honor of <a href="http://library.osu.edu/find/collections/byrd-polar-archives/byrd/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Admiral Richard E. Byrd</a>, America''s most famous polar explorer. There are <a href="http://bpcrc.osu.edu/groups" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">ten research groups</a> at BPCRC, along with a Library, <a href="http://library.osu.edu/find/collections/byrd-polar-archives" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Archival Program</a>, the <a href="http://research.bpcrc.osu.edu/rr/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Polar Rock Repository</a>, and a team of support staff. Research at the Center focuses on the role of cold regions in the Earth''s overall climate system, and encompasses geological sciences, geochemistry, glaciology, paleoclimatology, meteorology, remote sensing, ocean dynamics, and the history of polar exploration.<br>Today, the Byrd Polar Center will be lecturing about global climate change!', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-11-08T16:10:00', '2016-11-08T17:15:00', 2, 0),
(252, 'Inside Graduate Admissions: Merit, Diversity, and Faculty Gatekeeping', '1080 Physics Research Building - Smith Seminar Room ', 'How does graduate admissions work? Who does the system work for, and who falls through its cracks? Where does admissions reform fit into broader efforts to reduce inequalities in graduate education? In this talk, education professor Julie Posselt will pull back the curtain on admissions processes usually conducted in secret, and examine the limits and possibilities of rethinking admissions for increasing diversity in STEM. Drawing on more than five years of research that includes extensive observations of admission committees in action, Posselt will reveal how professors create and negotiate the meaning of merit as they evaluate applicants and work daily with their students. She will also show how departments that improve diversity through admissions and recruitment, but that lack strong mentoring relationships, may struggle to maintain gains serving underrepresented populations.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-08T16:00:00', '2016-11-08T17:00:00', 2, 0),
(251, 'Co-op Internship Research (CIR)', 'Caldwell Lab (Room 109)', '<em>This event is highly recommended for students in Biological and Chemical Science related areas and Mathematical and Engineering related areas.</em><br>Join the OHSE CIR Session and learn from OHSE scholars co-op, internship and research experiences. There will be t<strong>wo session and students may schoose wich to attend</strong>.<br>Agenda:<br />3:45-4:45 Biological and Chemical Sciences related areas<br />4:45-5:00 Break/Refreshments<br />5:00-5:45 Mathematical and Engineering related areas<br />5:45-6:00 Q&amp;A', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-08T15:45:00', '2016-11-08T18:00:00', 2, 0),
(250, 'Redefining the Path to Health Equity', 'Mershon Auditorium', '<em>The Provost''s Discovery Themes Lecture Program is recommended for all students.</em><br>David Satcher, MD, PhD, is the second person in history to simultaneously hold the positions of <strong>US Surgeon General and Assistant Secretary for Health</strong>. In these dual roles, he encouraged public debate about the importance of a balanced healthcare system and a wide range of related topics, including mental health, suicide, cloning, sex education and AIDS. Serving under both President Bill Clinton and President George H.W. Bush, he led efforts to eliminate racial and ethnic disparities in health.<br>To register, click <a href="http://discovery.osu.edu/about/provosts-discovery-themes-lecturer-program/david-satcher.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-08T15:30:00', '2016-11-08T16:45:00', 2, 0),
(249, 'Professional Development Workshop: Professional Small Talk & Networking', 'Student Alumni Council Room, Ohio Union', 'This workshop will teach student about the Power of the 3 Ps: Power, Presence and Perception and how to become more effective, engaged, and connected leaders. It’s not about collecting business cards. It’s about caring for others and establishing genuine connections. At the close of the event, participants will receive additional resources created by industry experts for continued development opportunities.<br>Facilitated by: Kwame Christian, Director of Community Relations Kirwan Institute on Race and Ethnicity<br>Kaylee Hartman<br>Student Activities - OUAB Grad/Prof <br><a href="mailto:hartman.557@osu.edu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">hartman.557@osu.edu</a><br>614-292-1274', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-08T12:00:00', '2016-11-08T13:00:00', 2, 0),
(248, 'Election Day', '', 'Go vote and make your voice heard! If you are registered in Franklin County, polls will be open from 6:30 am to 7:30 pm at the Ohio Union.<br>Be sure to be educated about your choices through resources like the ones below: <br><a href="http://onyourballot.vote411.org/index.do" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">On Your Ballot</a>, <a href="https://votesmart.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">VoteSmart</a>, <a href="https://ballotpedia.org/Main_Page" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Ballotpedia</a>', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-08T00:00:00', '2016-11-08T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(247, 'HSPB Trivia Night', 'Curl Market Viewpoint North', 'This month''s board will focus on topics in the <strong>presidential election process</strong>, so come prepared! Students from any Honors or Scholars group are welcome, and you are not required to come with a team, but space is limited, so please <a href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001MaJJupA-3MsVFTe_K38rI56FHXV3-iq_0Hjs0zpBvyX5eRuYKQyp4PtJhyhcnZRymLX-OWprIdK072zFdUumYME1h0QvSTZJdXl0ZWkfnNRmAKzWuiduyoP4ESg75FCuB23NE7OYxg7rKhX1ecTOsniG-eycWWcz1RC9L7FdmmI=&amp;c=xG3Ei_FDrgAMqTlDbxIrhMz9Sqpw0c1JDkNNfRFojy5kaWHTTocPOg==&amp;ch=sw5VYlLKwJsdFGOJH4krtYiVQxNwHZ-K12FAj5rQ52GvuQG-QjC6ew==" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">RSVP </a>.', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-11-07T18:30:00', '2016-11-07T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(245, 'The Case of the Missing Ribosome and Other Tales of Protein Translation', 'BRT 115 ', '<em>For students interested in the biological sciences</em><br>As part of its Host Pathogen Seminar Series, the Center for Microbial Interface Biology — along with co-sponsors <strong>Department of Microbial Infection and Immunity</strong>, Center for Retrovirus Research and Discovery Themes in Infectious Disease — will host Dr. Jonathan Yewdell, chief of the cellular biology section, Laboratory of Viral Diseases, NIAID, NIH. ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-07T16:00:00', '2016-11-07T17:00:00', 2, 0),
(246, 'Minority in Engineering Panel', 'Baker 144', 'Come listen to panelists Lisa Abrams, Latonia Stiner-Jones, and Alex Avendañoanswer your questions about what it''s like to be a minority in engineering and how to successfully navigate any obstacles you may face. Dinner will be provided so please RSVP below by Wednesday November 2nd!<br><a href="https://goo.gl/forms/kzkrgPa7QJ1FTs122" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://goo.gl/forms/kzkrgPa7QJ1FTs122</a>', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-07T18:30:00', '2016-11-07T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(243, 'Football vs Nebraska', '', 'null', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-05T20:00:00', '2016-11-05T23:45:00', 2, 0),
(244, 'Scholarship America Dream Award (For Sophomores and Up)', '', 'The Dream Award is Scholarship America’s renewable scholarship program for financially needy students who have overcome barriers and have successfully started their college education. Awards were made to students selected from across the nation who are entering their <strong>second year or higher of education beyond high school</strong>; the scholarships are both renewable and increase in amount each year. Scholarship America provides Dream Awards ranging from $5,000 to $15,000 based on the individual student’s financial need. Each student’s award will increase by $1,000 each year to help them successfully finish school and earn their degrees.<br>Dream Award scholarships for 2017-18 will include general scholarships, STEM-specific scholarships (for study in science, technology, engineering and math-related majors) and the World Journal Dream Award Scholarship for Chinese American students. Financial need will always be considered in determining award amounts.', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-11-07T00:00:00', '2016-11-07T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(241, 'De-stress Canvas Painting Night', 'Houston House Art Room', 'Come out and enjoy a night of canvas painting with your mentors!<br>There will be pizza and supplies, all you need is a creative imagination!<br>Please RSVP through the link provided, by Thursday October 27th, to ensure we have enough supplies and food. <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/X9NN88T" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/X9NN88T</a>', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-11-04T18:00:00', '2016-11-04T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(242, 'Web Workshop with Rockwell Automation', '260 Dreese Labs', '<em>This event is recommended for any students with interest in programming, including beginners. </em><br>Web Workshop with automation with React, Particle Photons, and Particle Cloud<br>Rockwell Automation is organizing a web development workshop involving putting together a single pager web app via React that reads data from IoT devices and displays it. There will be pizza and some prizes will be given out. If interested, please RSVP at <a href="http://go.osu.edu/rockwell" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">http://go.osu.edu/rockwell</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-05T11:15:00', '2016-11-05T15:00:00', 2, 0),
(238, 'OUAB Karaoke Night', ' Woody''s Tavern', 'null', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-03T19:00:00', '2016-11-03T21:30:00', 2, 0),
(239, 'How to Get a Job Saving the Planet', 'Scott, E100 ', 'Event dedicated for STEM students with an interest in environment.<br>Breakfast will be provided to interested students. If interested RSVP by clicking <a href="http://go.osu.edu/egoodstein" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-04T09:00:00', '2016-11-04T10:00:00', 2, 0),
(240, 'Chemical Abstracts Service: Technology Open House ', '2540 Olentangy River Road', 'This is a great opportunity to learn more about CAS, networking and to consider CAS as a future employer whether it be an internship or fulltime employment, particularly for CSE/CIS/Data Analytics and related majors. Check out the details on this <a href="http://bdaaatohiostate.us12.list-manage.com/track/click?u=142665677fc58bf1a34031807&amp;id=1db7008830&amp;e=6066988315" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">flyer.</a>', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-04T10:00:00', '2016-11-04T17:00:00', 2, 0),
(237, 'Republicans, Democrats and Sustainability: Recovering Bipartisan Environmental Politics', 'Knowlton Hall, Room 205', '<em>For any student interested in the enviroment and politics.</em><br>Events are sponsored by The Sustainable and Resilient Economy and SUSTAINS Learning Community.<br> ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-03T19:00:00', '2016-11-03T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(235, 'Women''s Volleyball', 'St. John Arena', 'null', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-02T20:00:00', '2016-11-02T22:00:00', 2, 0),
(236, 'Finding & Applying for Summer STEM Research Programs', 'Page Hall, 60', 'There are multitudes of<strong> national and international research programs for students in the STEM</strong> (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics) fields during the summer. Attend this session to learn what is out there and how to find programs, what is required to apply, and get insight and tips for a successful application from previous participants in summer undergraduate research programs.', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-11-03T17:30:00', '2016-11-03T18:30:00', 2, 0),
(234, 'Science Cafe: The Science of Election Prediction', '18th Avenue Library: Research Commons (3rd Floor)', '<em>This event will best suited for math and computer science majors</em><br><strong>Comparing election forecasting models</strong>, election stock markets, polls-of-polls, and other prediction systems for the 2016 U.S. presidential election. How should the quality of a prediction system be assessed? Which prediction systems have been most successful in the past? How useful can these predictions be in this most unpredictable election year?', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-02T18:30:00', '2016-11-02T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(232, 'Pre-Law Forum - Legal Careers Panel', 'Moritz College of Law, Saxbe Auditorium', '<em>Students interested in law-school</em><br>This is a great opportunity to hear from <strong>practicing attorneys</strong> about different areas of law and things to consider as you figure out what sort of attorney you may want to be. Be sure to ask questions regarding STEM and law.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-02T18:00:00', '2016-11-02T19:15:00', 2, 0),
(233, 'OUAB Flicks for Free ft. The Jungle Book', 'Ohio Union, U.S. Bank Conference Theater', '<em>The man-cub Mowgli flees the jungle after a threat from the tiger Shere Khan. Guided by Bagheera the panther and the bear Baloo, Mowgli embarks on a journey of self-discovery, though he also meets creatures who don''t have his best interests at heart. </em>', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-02T18:00:00', '2016-11-02T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(231, 'Professional School Information Night ', '', '<em>This event is for Second- and Third-Year Scholars interested in Professonal Schools</em><br> <br>The Biological Sciences, Health Sciences and STEM EE Scholars programs are collaborating to offer a <strong>Professional School Information Night</strong> to the upper-class scholars. In order to deliver an all-encompassing program, we will be offering multiple break-out sessions, so students can attend at least two professional schools’ presentations.<br> <br>To RSVP, click <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/TYx1r5IVAQ7J7gJj2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.<br> ', 'teamup', '2155500', '2016-11-02T17:00:00', '2016-11-02T18:30:00', 2, 0),
(230, 'Columbus Collaboratory Tech Talk', 'Hitchcock, 031', '<em>If you are familiar with the statistical platform R, this event will be interesting for you.</em><br>The Columbus Collaboratory will share some of the cutting edge technologies in development for their member companies, including a <strong>demo of CognizeR</strong>, the package developed for integrating IBM’s Watson into R.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-01T19:30:00', '2016-11-01T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(229, 'HSPB Buckeyes and Batons', 'Taylor Tower Lobby', 'Honors &amp; Scholars Board presents Buckeyes &amp; Batons: a clinic focused on baton twirling and leadership development. Come and join this collaboration between the Buckeye Twirl team and the Honors &amp; Scholars Programming Board on Tuesday, November 1 from 6:00 to 7:30 p.m. in Taylor Tower''s Lobby. Buckeye Donuts will be provided and no previous twirling experience or materials required--we will teach you all that you need to know! Wear something comfortable to move around in. Please state your interest by emailing <a href="mailto:hspb@osu.edu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">hspb@osu.edu</a>.', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-11-01T18:00:00', '2016-11-01T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(227, 'Dental Student Panel', 'Jennings 40 ', '<em>Event geared towards students interested in Dental School</em><br> <br><strong>Students in dental school</strong> will give their perspective and advice to undergraduate students pursuing a career in dentistry. RSVVP to Melissa Basford, Bio Sci Scholars, at basford.18@osu.edu.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-11-01T13:00:00', '2016-11-01T17:15:00', 2, 0),
(228, 'Arts & Sciences Career Services Resume Tips', 'Macquigg Laboratory 264', '<em>This event is recommended for students of all majors interested in resume tips</em><em>.</em><br>Bring a current version of your resume!', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-11-01T16:10:00', '2016-11-01T17:05:00', 2, 0),
(225, 'H&S Halloween Bash with Best Buddies', '', 'Are you excited to celebrate Halloween? Are you ready to wear your best costume and make some fun halloween crafts with some new friends? Then come to HSPB''s Halloween Bash with Best Buddies! Best Buddies is a student organization that works to link OSU students with students with a range of intellectual and developmental disabilities to form the best friendships. At this event, you will get the chance to learn more about the Best Buddies organization and have a halloween themed craft party with the members of the Best Buddies organization where you will make some halloween capes together. But space is limited so RSVP at <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/xZDNWknQdkH7kPil2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://goo.gl/forms/xZDNWknQdkH7kPil2</a> for more information about the event and the location.', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-10-31T18:30:00', '2016-10-31T20:30:00', 2, 0),
(226, 'Halloween Week Star Party', 'Roof of Smith Lab, access by stairs from planetarium, Smith Lab 5033', 'Attendees will be pointing out stars and the constellations, taking a look at Mars and Saturn and other sights through the telescopes.Cancelation of Roof Night may be due to weather and will be announced by 5pm for that day. The information will be posted on OSU Planetarium''s <a href="https://www.facebook.com/OSUPlanetarium/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Facebook page</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-31T19:00:00', '2016-11-02T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(223, 'American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics Scholarships', '', 'The AIAA Foundation annually awards financial aid through a <a href="http://www.aiaa.org/scholarshipsandawards/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">number of scholarships</a> to undergraduate and graduate students in science or engineering programs. These scholarships are particularly for those in aerospace-related majors, but the criteria are pretty broad.', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-10-31T00:00:00', '2016-10-31T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(224, 'SOLAR Foundation Undergraduate Research Awards', '', 'Recommended for undergraduate students pursuing <strong>research in the fields of epidemiology, virology, HIV and AIDS education, and other infections of the blood and related subjects</strong>.<br>The application is due <strong>Friday (12/2)</strong>. Read more at http://go.osu.edu/solarfund.', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-10-31T00:00:00', '2016-10-31T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(222, 'Women Transportation Seminar Sharon D. Memorial Scholarship', '', 'This scholarship is recommended for <strong>females in their second-year and up in engineering and other fields related to transportation</strong>.<br>Sharon D. Banks Memorial Scholarship (Undergraduate): Local Award - $1,000, National Award - $5,000<br><a href="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/0724670675ea259cb94841576/files/WTS_Scholarship_Letter_2016.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Deadine: November 11, 2016</a>', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-10-31T00:00:00', '2016-10-31T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(216, 'Residence Life Kickball Tournament (STEM Team)', 'Lincoln Tower Park Fields', 'Registration Information: There will be 9-12 players per team and up to 10 players on the field per inning. Each team must have at least 4 female players. Students interested contact Alex Orkis (<a href="mailto:orkis.6@buckeyemail.osu.edu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">orkis.6@buckeyemail.osu.edu</a>).', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-28T00:00:00', '2016-10-28T23:59:00', 2, 0),
