(203, 'STEM Jeopardy', 'Macquigg Laboratory 264', 'Come and join the fun with your STEM EE friends at this weeks Tuesday Event: STEM EE Jeopardy! Encourage all of your STEM peers to come because we will be working in teams of 3-5 people to play our STEM spin on Jeopardy. This will be a good chance to take a break from Midterm studying to play a fun game! The categories will be Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics, and Engagement &amp; Exploration so it is best to have one member of your team from each STEM house. ', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-10-25T16:10:00', '2016-10-25T17:05:00', 2, 0),
(202, 'The Science-Journalism Duality: Behind the Scenes at Scientific American', '1080 Physics Research Building - Smith Seminar Room', 'How did a (mostly) contented grad student running geophysical convection simulations wind up as a gatekeeper between science and the public? In this talk I''ll try to give a sense of what motivates science writers and editors, what exactly it is that we do, how we are navigating the turbulence in the publishing industry, and what it all means for the broader scientific community. I''ll naturally focus on <em>Scientific American </em>and other publications I’ve worked for, but I''ll comment on broader trends and offer thoughts and tips of use not just for writing a magazine article, but for any other writing or communications project you take on. One of the thorniest issues that science journalists face is how to make sense of scientific disagreements and avoid pitfalls such as false balance. I''ll offer some remarks, but I''m also interested in your thoughts and advice for how we journalists might do better.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-25T16:00:00', '2016-10-25T17:00:00', 2, 0),
(201, 'Bettering the World with Liz Bohannon', 'Ohio Union Performance Hall', 'Upon graduating college (and at the same age as most of us) Liz uprooted herself and moved to Uganda to take part in something bigger than herself to empower the women there to continue education past high school and earn a degree of their own. To do so, <strong>Liz created Sseko Designs to employ those women to create unique and vibrant merchandise.</strong> But more importantly Sseko gives them a financial avenue to pursue a college degree that will provide a platform to create change.<br><em>Get tickets FOR FREE at the Union Info Desk to come hear her message</em>', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-24T19:30:00', '2016-10-24T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(200, 'Adobe Research  Women-in-Technology Scholarship ', '', 'The Adobe Research Women-in-Technology Scholarship recognizes outstanding undergraduate female students anywhere in the world who are studying computer science or related degrees.<br>The Adobe Research Women-in-Technology Scholarship includes:<br><ul><br><li>A $10,000 award paid once.</li><br><li>A Creative Cloud subscription membership for one year.</li><br><li>An Adobe Research mentor.</li><br><li>An internship opportunity at Adobe for the 2017 summer.</li><br></ul><br><strong>Applications are due October 31, 2016</strong>, 5pm Pacific Time. A committee of Adobe researchers will review all applicants and select the winners at their discretion. Recipients are selected based on their academic record, a personal statement, and three letters of reference. Students may be invited for phone interviews following the initial review.', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-10-24T00:00:00', '2016-10-24T23:59:00', 2, 0),
