(199, 'Science Sundays: How Confidence Affects Decision Making and Action', 'Ohio Union U.S. Bank Conference Theatre', 'Although some people are more confident than others, nearly everyone wants to be more confident.  But why?  What good is confidence?   Petty explains where confidence comes from and the polarizing impact that it can have on our important judgments and behaviors.<br><em>Richard E. Petty, Distinguished University Professor of psychology at Ohio State, an expert on the impacts of social influence on judgment and behavior.</em><br>See <a href="https://artsandsciences.osu.edu/research/science-sundays" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Science Sundays</a> for more info.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-23T15:00:00', '2016-10-23T16:00:00', 2, 0),
(197, 'Ohio Avian Research Conference ', 'Granville, Ohio', '<em>For any student interested in learning about birds </em><br>This annual conference brings together professional ornithologists from museums and other academic institutions, high school, undergraduate, and graduate students, government agencies, as well as non-professional researchers and citizen scientists alike from all over Ohio to present and share their research projects with one another and with other interested individuals through oral and poster presentations (<a href="http://tuckercasey.wixsite.com/aacri-birds/oarc2016" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">conference info</a>). <strong>This event will count as two events.</strong>', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-22T00:00:00', '2016-10-22T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(196, 'OSU Night at COSI', 'COSI, 333 W Broad St', 'Free Admission to COSI with a valid BuckID. $5 COSI Bucks to the first 1000 guests. Continuous bus loop service from campus to COSI and back. beginning at 6:15 p.m. from the following CABS bus stops: Buckeye Village Community Center, Drake Performance Center, Haverfield House, Neil Building, Ohio Union. For more information contact Ryan Mouncey at <a href="mailto:mouncey.1@osu.edu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">mouncey.1@osu.edu</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-21T18:30:00', '2016-10-21T22:30:00', 2, 0),
(194, 'HSPB''s Dips of the World', 'Kuhn Honors & Scholars House', 'Honors &amp; Scholars Programming Board (HSPB) welcomes you to come and enjoy Dips of the World! Come and taste some delicious dips from around the world! You will be able to try dips such as hummus, salsa, and chutney. This event offers a fun, educational experience for H&amp;S students to explore different cultures through food. We hope to see you there!', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-10-20T17:00:00', '2016-10-20T18:00:00', 2, 0),
(195, 'HSPB Trivia Night', '', 'Do you enjoy trivia? How about free pizza and prizes? If so, don''t miss the second Honors &amp; Scholars Programming Board''s Trivia Night on Thursday, October 20! Join for a great evening of fun, fast paced activity, and a great chance to show off your trivia knowledge with your friends! This month''s board will focus on topics in history, so come prepared! Students from any Honors or Scholars group are welcome, and you are not required to come with a team, but space is limited, so please RSVP at <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfyub0VFE-uqEv4ZrFdcUMQKfk9oaUhwWMTmfFAVZYhtgErUw/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfyub0VFE-uqEv4ZrFdcUMQKfk9oaUhwWMTmfFAVZYhtgErUw/viewform</a>. ', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-10-20T18:30:00', '2016-10-20T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(192, 'OUAB Flicks for Free ft. Suicide Squad', 'Ohio Union, U.S. Bank Conference Theater', 'First show: 6 PM<br>Second show: 8:30 PM<br>Free popcorn and beverages will be provided!<br> <br><em>It feels good to be bad...Assemble a team of the world''s most dangerous, incarcerated Super Villains, provide them with the most powerful arsenal at the government''s disposal, and send them off on a mission to defeat an enigmatic, insuperable entity. U.S. intelligence officer Amanda Waller has determined only a secretly convened group of disparate, despicable individuals with next to nothing to lose will do. However, once they realize they weren''t picked to succeed but chosen for their patent culpability when they inevitably fail, will the Suicide Squad resolve to die trying, or decide it''s every man for himself?</em>', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-19T18:00:00', '2016-10-19T22:00:00', 2, 0),
(193, 'Newman Technology Tour', 'Mainsfield, Ohio', '<em>For students in engineering fields</em><br>Please sign-up for the trip by end of the day on <strong>Friday, October 7th,</strong> and no ''backsies'', after you have signed up. *Note for first year-scholars: Students attending the trip, will be excused from Scholars Seminar on the week of October 17th. RSVP, by clicking <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/Mta6i1V9WI1USAfE3" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.<br><strong>Company''s Desctiption</strong>:  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XdG1Eivtdmw#action=share" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XdG1Eivtdmw#action=share</a> ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-20T11:30:00', '2016-10-20T17:30:00', 2, 0),
(190, 'PSL Scholars Mock Presidential Debate', 'Moritz College of Law, Saxbe Auditorium', 'Join us the night of October 18 for the 2016 Mock Presidential Debate, featuring current PSL Scholar students portraying the VP and Presidential Candidates! Moderated by ABC6/Fox28 Political Reporter Ben Garbarek, the event will follow the Commission on Presidential Debates guidelines, but with an academic twist as we feature the nominees from the Democratic, Republican, *and* Libertarian parties! The VP Debate will begin at 7:00 p.m., followed by the Presidential Debate at approximately 7:40 p.m. Following the debates, join us in the Spin Room (the law school lounge) for refreshments and to meet the candidates!', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-10-18T19:00:00', '2016-10-18T20:30:00', 2, 0),
(191, 'Summer Research', 'Ramseyer 59', 'This event will focus on the <strong>summer interships</strong> available for students in the multple <strong>research</strong> fields. Addtionally, you will receive advice on how to be a successful applicant.<br> <br>If you are interested in attending, <strong>RSVP with Melissa Basford</strong>, Bio Sci Scholars Manager, at basford.18@osu.edu', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-19T16:30:00', '2016-10-19T17:30:00', 2, 0),
(189, 'Dennis Learning Center', 'Macquigg Laboratory 264', '<em>Event is recommended for all students</em><br>Exams can be a stressful experience. You have to learn the material, take a test in a finite time and wait for your grade to post. But if you are strategic about how you prepare for your exams, you can be confident any exam you take will turn out just fine.  In this event,<strong> you will learn the optimal ways to prepare for your exams</strong> and the best strategies to take different types of tests. ', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-10-18T16:10:00', '2016-10-18T17:05:00', 2, 0),
(188, 'College of Arts and Sciences Education Abroad Fair', 'Great Hall Meeting Room, Ohio Union', 'Learn about Arts and Sciences Education Abroad opportunities in 2017, including:<br><ul><br><li>Global May Programs in 9 countries: Bolivia, Brazil, China, Great Britain, Hungary, Morocco, New Zealand, Spain and Uganda</li><br><li>Berlin, Then and Now: People, Places, and Experiences</li><br><li>Culture, Society and History of Zimbabwe</li><br><li>The Brazilian Experience</li><br><li>The British Invasion</li><br><li>Shanghai, 1750-2050</li><br><li>Global Hotspots of the Early Modern World: Buenos Aires, Argentina</li><br><li>Scientific Roots in Europe</li><br><li>History and Archaeology of Medieval Ireland</li><br><li>Economics of Immigration</li><br><li>HIV in Context: Tanzania</li><br><li>Mapping Our World – Southern Scandinavia</li><br><li>Environmental Sustainability in Costa Rica</li><br></ul><br>Meet faculty resident directors and past education abroad participants and learn about these and <strong>many other education abroad programs</strong>.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-18T06:00:00', '2016-10-18T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(186, 'Sustainable Energy Phenomena from First Principles: From Fuel Cells to Fusion', '2004 Evans', '<em>This event is recommended for engineering students</em><br><strong>Emily A. Carter</strong> is the Dean of the School of Engineering and Applied Science and the Gerhard R. Andlinger Professor in Energy and the Environment, as well as a Professor of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering and Applied and Computational Mathematics at Princeton University. Her current research is focused entirely on enabling discovery and design of materials for sustainable energy. ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-17T16:10:00', '2016-10-17T17:00:00', 2, 0),
