(176, 'Climate Change, the Anthropocene and the Deep History of the Earth', 'Columbus Museum of Art, The Forum', '<em>Should be interesting for all students</em><br> <br>What is the evidence for <strong>human-driven climate change in recent history</strong>? What is coming to be called the “Anthropocene”? Brooke will provide a layman’s overview and briefly comment on the way forward for humanity. ', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-13T19:00:00', '2016-10-13T21:00:00', 2, 0),
(173, 'Wingin'' It: How my science career took flight', 'Macquigg Laboratory 264', '<em>This event will be fantastic for pre-health students and students who are exploring different majors </em><br> <br>Jessica Caton, will be talking about her childhood goals of becoming a <strong>veterinarian</strong> and how that goal took her into different opportunities working with birds. She will also talk about transferable skills that she learned in college to work in outreach programs.', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-10-11T16:10:00', '2016-10-11T17:05:00', 2, 0),
