(172, 'Women''s Self Defense Seminar', 'Women''s Field House', '<em>This event is designed for women in order to identify risk factors for women on a college campus.</em><br> <br>The Honors and Scholars Programing Board presents the Women''s Self Defense Seminar. The seminar is being given by Kim Valemore, a <strong>second degree black belt</strong> in Taekwondo. his event is open to all students who identify as women or non-binary, and is meant to be a safe space for you to feel comfortable discussing issues that impact women. Feel free to bring a partner because there will be a lot of partner work, but no partner is required to participate!<br>RSVP <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScj6xHUA6_uRpgb_hAYAiTVftHSkPjlSnH8-VEv2z8Vj7ED3g/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>, for more details and location.', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-10-11T16:00:00', '2016-10-11T17:15:00', 2, 0),
(171, 'Caterpillar: Becoming the Employee of Choice', 'Journalism Building Rm 270', '<em>This event is hosted by the SWE (Society of Women Engineers), SHPE (Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers), and NSBE (National Society of Black Engineers) and is recommended for engineering, data analytics, and actuarial science majors. </em><br>Come listen to Tori Rollings, manager for Caterpillar’s Assurance of Supply Center (ASC) talk about how to be successful and be the employee of choice. Also in attendance will be Cheryl Verbeke, VP for Caterpillar Innovation<br>Tori Rollings is currently manager for Caterpillar’s Assurance of Supply Center (ASC). Her team uses analytics, big data, problem solving and business acumen to understand the Caterpillar Production Network and to identify, solve and prevent issues in the future.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-10T18:30:00', '2016-10-10T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(170, 'Current and Future U.S. Long-Baseline Neutrino Experiments: NOvA and DUNE', 'Physics Research Building, 4138', '<em>Seminar is for Physics students</em><br> <br><strong>Description of talk</strong>: Long-baseline neutrino experiments study beams of neutrinos near their source and at a far detector several hundred kilometers away. We study the changes in the beams between their generation and detection at the far detector.  Neutrinos come in three flavors: electron, muon, and tau. Our experiments produce a beam of muon neutrinos; as they travel, some of them “oscillate” into the other two kinds. By measuring the parameters that govern this oscillation, we gain a deeper understanding of the foundational laws that govern the material Universe.<br> <br>For more information, click <a href="https://physics.osu.edu/events/high-energy-physics-seminar-luke-corwin-south-dakota-school-mines-current-and-future-u.s." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-10T15:00:00', '2016-10-10T16:00:00', 2, 0),
