(169, 'Exploring Majors Fair: Engineering and Beyond', 'Physics Research Building Atrium', '<em>This will be a great event for all students</em><br> <br>Want to find a class to take next semester to explore a major? If so, join the 2016 Exploring Majors Fair! Stop by and <strong>chat with advisors</strong> and students from a variety of STEM related academic areas in one convenient location, right before scheduling classes for next semester starts!<br> <br>Aeronautical and Astronautical Engineering<br />Atmospheric Sciences, Geographic Information Science, Air Transportation Geography<br />Aviation<br />Biomedical Engineering<br />Business (Fisher College of)<br />Chemical and Biomolecular Engineering<br />Chemistry<br />Civil and Environmental Engineering<br />Computer Science and Engineering<br />Data Analytics<br />Earth Sciences<br />Education and Human Ecology (Exercise Science, Human Nutrition, STEM Education)<br />Electrical and Computer Engineering<br />Entomology<br />Environment and Natural Resources (Environment, Economy, Development and Sustainability; Environmental Sciences; Environmental Policy and Decision Making)<br />Food, Agricultural, Biological and Ecological Engineering<br />Food, Agriculture, and Environmental Sciences<br />Industrial and Systems Engineering<br />Knowlton School of Architecture<br />Languages, Literatures and Cultures<br />Materials Science and Engineering<br />Mathematics and Actuarial Sciences<br />Mechanical Engineering<br />Physics and Engineering Physics<br />Pre-Health<br />Pre-Law<br />Undergraduate Research', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-10T11:00:00', '2016-10-10T14:00:00', 2, 0),
(167, 'Corn Maze', '', '<em>Event is recommended for any scholar. </em><br> <br>We will be participating in some Fall fun with three other Scholars programs. The event will be on a Friday and the cost is <strong>$5,</strong> which includes your <strong>transportation, access to the maze, a hay ride, a small pumpkin, and other activities</strong>.<br> <br>Please <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/npT43mSWKp814c9r2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">RSVP</a> and pay no later than 9/26 (space is limited, so first come, first serve!)', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-07T16:30:00', '2016-10-07T20:30:00', 2, 0),
(166, 'Proton-Coupled Electron Transfer Chemistry of Energy Conversion Catalysis', 'CBEC 130', '<em>This event might be of high interest for students in science and engineering.</em><br> <br>Hughes to speak for October Emeritus Professor Nocera s the <strong>Patterson Rockwood Professor of Energy at Harvard</strong> and he is widely recognized as one of the <strong>world’s leading researchers in renewable energy</strong>. His group has pioneered studies of the basic mechanisms of energy conversion in biology and chemistry. He accomplished a solar fuels process of photosynthesis–the splitting of water to hydrogen and oxygen using sunlight and translated this science to produce the artificial leaf, which was named by Time magazine as Innovation of the Year for 2011. <br> <br>For more information, click <a href="http://chemistry.osu.edu/seminars/evans/2016" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-07T16:10:00', '2016-10-07T17:30:00', 2, 0),
