(162, 'A Complete Artificial Photosynthesis', 'McPherson 1000', '<em>This event might be of high interest for students in science and engineering.</em><br> <br>Hughes to speak for October Emeritus Professor Nocera s the <strong>Patterson Rockwood Professor of Energy at Harvard</strong> and he is widely recognized as one of the <strong>world’s leading researchers in renewable energy</strong>. His group has pioneered studies of the basic mechanisms of energy conversion in biology and chemistry. He accomplished a solar fuels process of photosynthesis–the splitting of water to hydrogen and oxygen using sunlight and translated this science to produce the artificial leaf, which was named by Time magazine as Innovation of the Year for 2011. <br> <br>For more information, click <a href="http://chemistry.osu.edu/seminars/evans/2016" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-06T16:00:00', '2016-10-06T17:15:00', 2, 0),
(161, 'Pre-Health Collegium Speaker', 'Hagerty Hall 071', '<em>This event will be useful for students interested in medical school</em><br> <br>Elana is a Collegium Alumni, graduating from Ohio State in 2016, and is <strong>currently an MD student at the Ohio State School of Medicine</strong>. Elana will be discussing her experience as a Pre-Med student at Ohio State, the medical school admissions process, and her time so far as a medical student and will be available for Q&amp;A<br> <br>To attend this event, RSVP <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScNXBkX5Pkm-IAujlWtR6tPa7fV0qCL7Cmmov53KuP8cSNd5Q/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-10-05T18:30:00', '2016-10-05T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(160, 'Science Cafe: The Microbiome in Health and Disease: Bugs, Guts, and Drugs', '18th Avenue Library (Research Commons in 3rd Floor) ', '<em>Students in pre-medical fields, biology, and similar fields are encouraged to attend.</em><br>Topic: <strong>The Microbiome in Health and Disease: Bugs, Guts, and Drugs</strong><br>Dr. Nicole Kwiek is a Clinical Assistant Professor of Pharmacology and the Director of Undergraduate Studies at the Ohio State University College of Pharmacy. She is also the Director of the Generation Rx Laboratory at the Center of Science and Industry (COSI) and co-leads the Generation Rx Initiative, a learning community of OSU faculty, staff, and students studying the problem of prescription drug misuse.<br>Visit the <a href="https://library.osu.edu/news/science-cafe/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">Science Cafe website</a> for more info!', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-05T18:30:00', '2016-10-05T19:30:00', 2, 0),
(159, 'OUAB Flicks for Free ft. Nerve', 'U.S. Bank Conference Theater, Ohio Union', 'First show: 6 PM<br>Second show: 8:30 PM<br>Location: U.S. Bank Conference Theater (Ohio Union)<br>Free popcorn and beverages will be provided!<br> <br><em>Lou Clark knows lots of things. She knows how many footsteps there are between the bus stop and home. She knows she likes working in The Buttered Bun tea shop and she knows she might not love her boyfriend Patrick. What Lou doesn''t know is she''s about to lose her job or that knowing what''s coming is what keeps her sane. Will Traynor knows his motorcycle accident took away his desire to live. He knows everything feels very small and rather joyless now and he knows exactly how he''s going to put a stop to that. What Will doesn''t know is that Lou is about to burst into his world in a riot of color. And neither of them knows they''re going to change each other for all time</em>', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-05T18:00:00', '2016-10-05T22:00:00', 2, 0),
