(157, 'Budgeting and Financial Goal Setting', 'Barbie Tootle Room, Ohio Union', '<em>For all students seeking better grasp of personal finances</em><br> <br>One of the most important aspects of<strong> financial wellness</strong> is an understanding of the basics.  This workshop will help you to start on your path to greater financial capability and understanding!  Topics include: budgeting, banking and credit.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-05T12:00:00', '2016-10-05T13:00:00', 2, 0),
(156, 'Healthcare-Associated Infections: A Personal and Public Healthcare Tragedy', 'Faculty Club, Grand Lounge', '<em>This event is suited for students with an interest in health-related careers</em><br> <br>Hughes to speak for October Emeritus Academy. His presentation will centered on <strong>healthcare-associated infections</strong>. To assist to this event, you must RSVP.<br> <br>To RSVP, click <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScKolY2-jIKlPttAFXe0fBr-XB5oOHguGOE5lHi3cAFhIzcZg/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-05T04:00:00', '2016-10-05T05:30:00', 2, 0),
(153, 'Actuarial Science and Risk Management ', 'Cockins Hall 240', '<em>For students in actuarial science</em><br> <br>Representatives of diffrent companies will have <strong>presentations on different areas of actuarial and risk management practices</strong>, will talk about the business, organization, and culture of their companies, and will explain what they are expecting from a candidate.', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-03T18:30:00', '2016-10-03T20:00:00', 2, 0),
(154, 'Scavenger Hunt', 'Campus', 'Scholars, feel free to use this time to work on completing the scavenger hunt. The scavenger hunt counts as an STEM EE Scholars event that you can log. ', 'teamup', '836634', '2016-10-04T16:10:00', '2016-10-04T17:05:00', 2, 0),
(155, 'Anatomy Graduate Program Eat and Explore', 'Jennings 140', '<em>This program is geared for students interested in Anatomy Graduate Programs</em><br> <br><strong>RSVP with Melissa Basford</strong>, Bio Sci Scholars, at  basford.18@osu.edu', 'teamup', '2155517', '2016-10-04T17:30:00', '2016-10-04T18:30:00', 2, 0),
(152, 'Wellness Ambassador', '', '<em>For students interested in  health sciences or looking for a long-term event.</em><br> <br>Wellness Ambassadors serve as a liaison between Student Life and other students on campus. Wellness Ambassadors play a vital role in supporting the mission of Student Life, which aims to<strong> promote wellness among Ohio State students and their communities</strong>. Wellness Ambassadors deliver educational presentations in a variety of settings and work as a team to develop and implement events highlighting the 9 dimensions of wellness. <br> <br>Applications due, on Sunday, October 30.  For more information, click <a href="https://swc.osu.edu/wellness-initiatives/wellness-ambassadors/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">here</a>.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-03T00:00:00', '2016-10-03T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(151, 'SMART Scholarship', '', '<em>This is a STEM Scholarship for all undergrad students, specifically those interested in Department of Defense labs. Note the conditions of appointment require you to be willing to accept post-graduate emplloyement with the DoD.</em><br>The Science, Mathematics And Research for Transformation (SMART) Scholarship for Service Program is an opportunity for students pursuing an undergraduate or graduate degree in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics (STEM) disciplines to receive a full scholarship and be gainfully employed upon degree completion. Students pursuing degrees related to the following are encouraged to apply:<br><em>*Students who are currently Freshman or enrolled in a First Year Associate’s Program applicants must report an ACT or SAT Reasoning Test Score. Subject tests are not required. In addition, individuals who apply during their Freshman/First Year must obtain a minimum cumulative 3.0 GPA on a 4.0 scale during the fall academic term of their Freshman/First Year. Freshman/First Year Associate''s Program applicants will be required to submit an official transcript reflecting their fall academic term grades to establish compliance with this requirement.</em><br><a href="http://smart.asee.org/apply_/application_instructions" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">http://smart.asee.org/apply_/application_instructions</a> ', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-10-03T00:00:00', '2016-10-03T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(149, 'Men''s Ice Hockey vs. Wilfrid Laurier', '', 'null', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-02T16:00:00', '2016-10-02T18:30:00', 2, 0),
(150, 'Autumn Enrichment Grant Applications ', '', '<em>Due November 25, 2016</em><br> <br>Apply for an Honors &amp; Scholars Enrichment Grant! The scholarship amount will range based on the student''s proposal, with <strong>a maximum award of $3,000</strong>, and will be awarded through a competitive application process. Funds can be utilized for a variety of purposes, including, but not limited to research, creative work and study abroad. <br> <br>For more information visit H&amp;S <a href="http://honors-scholars.osu.edu/current-students/opportunities" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">website</a> or contact Lindsey Chamberlain at  chamberlain.55@osu.edu.', 'teamup', '2193528', '2016-10-03T00:00:00', '2016-10-03T23:59:00', 2, 0),
(148, 'Running Water 5k & 10k', 'OSU RPAC', 'The event is a <strong>5K/10K</strong> race that people can do individually or in teams of four.  People can also walk or run carrying the pack filled with water to understand what it is like to have to carry water for several miles.  A really good article from NPR highlights this in case you are interested:  <a href="http://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2016/07/07/484793736/millions-of-women-take-a-long-walk-with-a-40-pound-water-can" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">http://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2016/07/07/484793736/millions-of-women-take-a-long-walk-with-a-40-pound-water-can</a>.<br> <br>To actually register for the race, folks can go to <strong>Premier Races</strong> at <a href="https://premierraces.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external">https://premierraces.com/</a>.  Any assistance with getting the word out via social media or word of mouth would be greatly, greatly appreciated.  We are aiming to have 50-100 people for this considering it is our first year.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-10-02T08:00:00', '2016-10-02T11:00:00', 2, 0),
(285, 'HSPB Service Snowman', 'Torres, Park-Stradley, Smith-Steeb, Taylor Tower, and Kuhn House', 'Want to give a kid a reason to smile? Want to make a child’s holiday season? HSPB is throwing a two-week long event from November 21st-December 2nd 12am-4pm called Service Snowman. In Torres, Park-Stradley, Smith-Steeb, Taylor Tower, and the Kuhn House there will be a snowman hanging up in the lobby. All you have to do is grab a tag, go out and buy the gift on the tag and return it to any of the designated locations above. It is a perfect thing to do over thanksgiving day break! Go out and make a little kids holiday season!', 'teamup', '979004', '2016-11-21T00:00:00', '2016-12-02T16:00:00', 2, 0),
(286, 'Thanksgiving Break - No Classes', '', 'No classes, offices closed.', 'teamup', '836635', '2016-11-23T00:00:00', '2016-11-25T23:59:00', 2, 0),
